1
00:00:07,174 --> 00:00:10,111
⟨I spent days full of love with 50 people who love me →

2
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:12,113
Detective Manami Tanizaki⟩

3
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:14,115
⟨To protect my love from danger →

4
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:16,617
Manami gathers them at the pension →

5
00:00:16,684 --> 00:00:18,619
In a strange communal life →

6
00:00:18,686 --> 00:00:21,622
My love is killed in the pension⟩

7
00:00:21,689 --> 00:00:24,125
⟨Huh? Is the mastermind behind the pension? ⟩

8
00:00:24,191 --> 00:00:25,626
(Speaker) (Voice changer) This is Ai-chan.

9
00:00:25,693 --> 00:00:29,196
(Speaker) This person was killed.

10
00:00:33,734 --> 00:00:35,669
(Kuroiwa) Ai-chan…｡

11
00:00:35,736 --> 00:00:38,172
(Erasaki) Do you know? (Kuroiwa) Past serial murders →

12
00:00:38,239 --> 00:00:40,241
This is the person who gave instructions behind the scenes.

13
00:00:44,745 --> 00:00:47,681
(Sakatani) Looks like the line is dead.

14
00:00:47,748 --> 00:00:51,685
(Wanibuchi) Can you stay in a place like this?

15
00:00:51,752 --> 00:00:53,254
(Kuroiwa) Hey!

16
00:00:54,255 --> 00:00:58,759
(Erasaki) This is... Wani-chan is going to be killed as a demonstration, right?

17
00:01:00,261 --> 00:01:02,196
(Kuroiwa) That's how I feel!

18
00:01:02,263 --> 00:01:04,131
Mr. Wanibuchi, don't move on your own!

19
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:06,133
(Wanibuchi) Noisy! It's more dangerous to stay here!

20
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,636
(Speaker) You can't go outside.

21
00:01:08,702 --> 00:01:11,205
(Speaker) You will die like EITO.

22
00:01:12,706 --> 00:01:16,143
(Wanibuchi: Loudly) A rat in a bag... huh?

23
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:18,646
(Kuroiwa) I think it feels different now.

24
00:01:18,712 --> 00:01:20,648
(Wanibuchi) Shit!

25
00:01:20,714 --> 00:01:26,654
♪～

26
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:29,156
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san, were you there? (Manami) Yes.

27
00:01:29,223 --> 00:01:32,660
Kuroiwa-kun, I was in the room planning to take turns when he came.→

28
00:01:32,726 --> 00:01:35,162
The camera footage in the room also fell down →

29
00:01:35,229 --> 00:01:37,665
It's completely blocked.

30
00:01:37,731 --> 00:01:41,168
(Kuroiwa) Ai-chan is in this building...

31
00:01:41,235 --> 00:01:45,172
(Speaker) I am the person who approaches Manami Tanizaki→

32
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:48,175
We will completely eliminate it.

33
00:01:48,242 --> 00:01:50,177
(Manami) Stop hiding and come out.

34
00:01:50,244 --> 00:01:53,180
(Speaker) I could kill you all at once, but →

35
00:01:53,247 --> 00:01:56,183
That's bland, isn't it?

36
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:57,685
(Manami) Huh?

37
00:01:57,751 --> 00:02:02,189
(Speaker) So I'm going to give you all a chance to get out of here.

38
00:02:02,256 --> 00:02:04,124
chance?

39
00:02:04,191 --> 00:02:06,627
(Speaker) If you kill someone in my love →

40
00:02:06,694 --> 00:02:08,629
Allow me to go outside.

41
00:02:08,696 --> 00:02:10,130
(Manami) Huh?

42
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:12,132
(Speaker) Ah, about the two detectives →

43
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:14,201
Please don't kill me.

44
00:02:15,703 --> 00:02:17,204
Broadcast room.

45
00:02:18,706 --> 00:02:21,141
(Manami) Hey... Sakatani-kun!

46
00:02:21,208 --> 00:02:24,645
(Speaker) Time limit is 24 hours.

47
00:02:24,712 --> 00:02:29,149
(Speaker) If no one dies after 24 hours→

48
00:02:29,216 --> 00:02:32,653
I'll kill someone again.

49
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,222
(Speaker) Let's start!

50
00:02:37,224 --> 00:02:40,661
Ha, there was no one there, ha...

51
00:02:40,728 --> 00:02:45,666
Maybe you're accessing the speakers from another part of the building.

52
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,668
(in a natural voice) I mean, what? Now.

53
00:02:47,735 --> 00:02:49,670
I can't speak normally. >> My voice is thin.

54
00:02:49,737 --> 00:02:51,171
(Wanibuchi's cough)

55
00:02:51,238 --> 00:02:54,174
EITO was suddenly gathered and killed too →

56
00:02:54,241 --> 00:02:56,677
A strange game of killing each other begins →

57
00:02:56,744 --> 00:02:58,746
What should I do...

58
00:03:02,249 --> 00:03:04,118
(Kuroiwa) It's okay!

59
00:03:04,184 --> 00:03:07,621
Manami is a top-notch detective.

60
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:11,625
He is a regular at the Special Investigation Headquarters, and is usually called upon when difficult cases occur.

61
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:14,128
(All) Huh? (Manami) Eh...｡

62
00:03:14,195 --> 00:03:16,630
Aren't you a little surprised?

63
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:18,632
Isn't that rude?

64
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:22,636
(Kuroiwa) That person will do his or her best for you.

65
00:03:22,703 --> 00:03:24,638
Please believe me.

66
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:26,640
(Manami) Please!

67
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:31,145
Never... don't kill anyone.

68
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:42,656
♪～

69
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:45,659
(Manami) Ai-chan took E-chan away →

70
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:49,229
It's hidden somewhere in this building.

71
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:54,234
No... it's the worst.

72
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:59,740
If I didn't collect them here...

73
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:06,180
(Kuroiwa) He might have been killed by Ai-chan sooner.

74
00:04:08,682 --> 00:04:11,619
I think Manami is doing her best.

75
00:04:11,685 --> 00:04:14,688
For now, let's focus on stopping Ai-chan.

76
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,691
(Manami) Yeah...｡

77
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:27,134
(Manami) Huh?

78
00:04:27,201 --> 00:04:31,205
(Kuroiwa) Did you find anything? (Manami) Something that should be there isn't...

79
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:38,145
(sound like a cry)

80
00:04:38,212 --> 00:04:40,714
(Kuroiwa) What next? (Sound like a cry)

81
00:04:42,216 --> 00:04:44,151
(Manami) In the south-southeast direction →

82
00:04:44,218 --> 00:04:46,654
Deer are mating. (deer sounds)

83
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,656
(Kuroiwa) What? (deer cry)

84
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:54,662
(Manami) Right now, my five senses are starting to become sharper...

85
00:04:54,728 --> 00:04:56,664
[Wow! ] (Kuroiwa's voice) My patience is at its limit →

86
00:04:56,730 --> 00:04:58,666
It felt like...

87
00:04:58,732 --> 00:05:01,168
what? that.

88
00:05:01,235 --> 00:05:06,607
(Manami) Apparently there's a pressure point around here that suppresses sexual desire.

89
00:05:06,674 --> 00:05:10,110
(Kuroiwa) Huh~ (Manami) When it gets high, here →

90
00:05:10,177 --> 00:05:13,113
Press... Uh...｡

91
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:16,183
(Kuroiwa) Yes, please do your best.

92
00:05:18,686 --> 00:05:21,121
(Emoto) Less. Huh? Ah~｡

93
00:05:21,188 --> 00:05:24,124
Isn't it enough to eat evenly?

94
00:05:24,191 --> 00:05:26,627
I see...

95
00:05:26,694 --> 00:05:30,130
The only thing I was particular about was EITO.

96
00:05:30,197 --> 00:05:35,636
It was really troublesome for the celebrity to have dietary restrictions.

97
00:05:35,703 --> 00:05:39,139
(Manami) I couldn't eat it.

98
00:05:39,206 --> 00:05:42,142
(Erasaki) What do you mean? (Manami) Due to a chronic illness.

99
00:05:42,209 --> 00:05:44,144
(Erasaki) Seriously?

100
00:05:44,211 --> 00:05:48,148
(Manami) It seems like she had dietary restrictions since she was little.

101
00:05:48,215 --> 00:05:52,219
I also had to take medicine at regular intervals.

102
00:05:53,721 --> 00:05:56,657
(Manami's voice) Recently, my symptoms have gotten worse →

103
00:05:56,724 --> 00:05:58,659
The amount of medication was also increasing.

104
00:05:58,726 --> 00:06:01,729
(Sakatani's voice) It's not like that at all...

105
00:06:03,163 --> 00:06:05,099
(Manami) [Are you okay? ]

106
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:07,101
[Today's live, right? ]

107
00:06:07,167 --> 00:06:09,103
(EITO) [Okay]

108
00:06:09,169 --> 00:06:11,171
(EITO) [Because it has nothing to do with the fans]

109
00:06:14,174 --> 00:06:16,110
[90% of glitter is →

110
00:06:16,176 --> 00:06:19,113
It's made of slimy, thin skin.]

111
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:24,118
(Manami) She was a person who struggled to pretend that nothing was wrong.

112
00:06:24,184 --> 00:06:27,121
(EITO) [It's easy to say I'll start over...]

113
00:06:27,187 --> 00:06:31,125
[You only live once and it will be over in a blink of an eye]

114
00:06:31,191 --> 00:06:34,194
It's pretty cool.

115
00:06:36,196 --> 00:06:39,633
(Kuroiwa) The medicine was missing from Mr. EITO's room.

116
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:42,136
That's probably the cause of death.

117
00:06:42,202 --> 00:06:43,704
>> Huh?

118
00:06:45,205 --> 00:06:50,711
(Manami) It's possible that someone intentionally took the medicine with them.

119
00:06:59,019 --> 00:07:01,455
(Wanibuchi) Who is Ai-chan?

120
00:07:01,522 --> 00:07:04,525
(Tokujii) Isn't there such a thing as a curse?

121
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:09,763
(Tokujii) Shrine in this forest→

122
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:12,266
The name of the god worshiped is →

123
00:07:12,332 --> 00:07:16,770
Aizen Jiannei Myoo.

124
00:07:16,837 --> 00:07:18,772
(Wanibuchi) Wait a minute! In short →

125
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:21,275
Ai-chan. (Erasaki) Are you being too pushy?

126
00:07:21,341 --> 00:07:23,343
(Wanibuchi) Huh? Wait...

127
00:07:24,845 --> 00:07:26,780
this!

128
00:07:26,847 --> 00:07:28,782
(Tokujii) "Ai-chan". (Erasaki) No, no...

129
00:07:28,849 --> 00:07:31,285
EITO also appeared as a guest in this drama.

130
00:07:31,351 --> 00:07:33,787
Maybe there is a hint about the role name or development...

131
00:07:33,854 --> 00:07:35,789
(Erasaki) No, wait a moment and do that →

132
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:38,292
What do you think about that curse thing? (Tokujii) Hmm...｡

133
00:07:38,358 --> 00:07:41,295
No! Nothing if it's only episode 7...

134
00:07:41,361 --> 00:07:44,798
(Sakatani) What's the next script? >> I don't have it, only the script for episode 7.

135
00:07:44,865 --> 00:07:46,800
(Sakatani) Huh?

136
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:50,304
Because he was an extra...

137
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,306
(Sakatani) Huh…｡

138
00:07:52,372 --> 00:07:54,308
What have you been doing all this time? Even though there's no internet.

139
00:07:54,374 --> 00:07:56,310
I'm looking for another line.

140
00:07:56,376 --> 00:07:58,812
If I can get in touch with the outside world, I might be able to get out of here.

141
00:07:58,879 --> 00:08:01,315
(Sound of typing on keyboard) Hmph... Yes... Thank you.

142
00:08:01,381 --> 00:08:03,450
(sound of typing on keyboard) Icchan, you're doing everything right.

143
00:08:03,517 --> 00:08:09,490
(Manami) Huh... I don't think anyone is Ai-chan after all.

144
00:08:09,556 --> 00:08:14,494
Everyone, don't kill someone and get out of here →

145
00:08:14,561 --> 00:08:16,997
I'm thinking about how to survive.

146
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:19,499
Because those are the people.

147
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:23,003
(Kuroiwa) That's why I would like to hear the facts.

148
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:25,072
As a detective.

149
00:08:27,074 --> 00:08:29,009
This is to confirm.

150
00:08:29,076 --> 00:08:32,012
Not all of you are Ai-chan.

151
00:08:32,079 --> 00:08:34,948
(Manami) Yes, I understand.

152
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:36,950
Well then, let's split up.

153
00:08:37,017 --> 00:08:40,954
(Kuroiwa) No... Manami-san, please sort out the incident situation here.

154
00:08:41,021 --> 00:08:43,957
(Manami) Eh, but aren't the two of you faster?

155
00:08:44,024 --> 00:08:46,460
(Kuroiwa) Huh... When I'm alone with my love →

156
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:48,962
I don't know what to do, right? Manami-san.

157
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:51,965
(Manami) Hehehe... Huh? As expected…｡

158
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:55,535
As a detective, I will protect the line...

159
00:08:56,537 --> 00:08:58,472
Please. (Kuroiwa) Yes.

160
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:00,974
(Erasaki) Yes!

161
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:03,977
(Manami) Ah, I'm tired. >> I'm tired.

162
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,979
Interview finished!

163
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:07,981
Good! (Manami) Sorry! a little bit….

164
00:09:08,048 --> 00:09:10,484
>> What? A restraining order?

165
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:14,988
(Manami) I don't know what you'll do if I approach you.

166
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:17,057
>> What is that?

167
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,060
You know...

168
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:25,999
What about killing me?

169
00:09:26,066 --> 00:09:29,002
(Manami) Huh...what are you talking about?

170
00:09:29,069 --> 00:09:32,005
>> Huh... I... →

171
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:34,074
You're a murderer.

172
00:09:35,509 --> 00:09:38,946
I used to box when I was in high school.

173
00:09:39,012 --> 00:09:41,448
Even if my opponent falls down→

174
00:09:41,515 --> 00:09:44,017
I hit my head and stayed there...

175
00:09:46,019 --> 00:09:48,522
(Manami) That was an accident.

176
00:09:50,023 --> 00:09:54,461
>> But something has always been bothering me.

177
00:09:54,528 --> 00:09:57,531
Even if I become a monk or drink alcohol...

178
00:09:59,032 --> 00:10:04,471
No matter who dies, no matter who kills Manami, she'll be sad, right?

179
00:10:04,538 --> 00:10:07,040
I can't stand looking at that.

180
00:10:09,042 --> 00:10:13,981
(Manami) Eryan is always talking about people.

181
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:17,985
Well, that's the good part...

182
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:20,487
That's different.

183
00:10:20,554 --> 00:10:23,490
>> If I had to die anyway, it would be for Manami-chan →

184
00:10:23,557 --> 00:10:25,492
That's what I was thinking.

185
00:10:25,559 --> 00:10:27,561
I thought it was just right!

186
00:10:30,063 --> 00:10:31,999
(Sound of a pat on the back)

187
00:10:32,065 --> 00:10:35,936
I won't forgive you if you die.

188
00:10:36,003 --> 00:10:37,938
>> Hmph…｡

189
00:10:38,005 --> 00:10:41,942
Despite the cuteness...I'm going to die once.

190
00:10:42,009 --> 00:11:02,529
♪～

191
00:11:08,035 --> 00:11:09,970
(Sound of keyboard hitting)

192
00:11:10,037 --> 00:11:11,972
(Wanibuchi) This...

193
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:14,975
If no one dies by tomorrow evening →

194
00:11:15,042 --> 00:11:19,980
Does that mean Ai-chan is coming to kill me? Isn't it dangerous?

195
00:11:20,047 --> 00:11:21,982
Rather than coming to kill →

196
00:11:22,049 --> 00:11:25,485
Is there a possibility that Ai-chan is among them?

197
00:11:25,552 --> 00:11:28,989
In fact, EITO Niki's attitude here was the worst, wasn't it?

198
00:11:29,056 --> 00:11:31,558
(sound of typing on keyboard) People who have no reason to kill...

199
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:34,995
I guess he's not there.

200
00:11:36,496 --> 00:11:38,932
(Erasaki) But if you say so→

201
00:11:38,999 --> 00:11:41,935
Emo-san is so suspicious.

202
00:11:42,002 --> 00:11:43,937
He threw it so flamboyantly.

203
00:11:44,004 --> 00:11:46,006
Does it make you want to kill him?

204
00:11:47,507 --> 00:11:49,509
You're used to that kind of thing.

205
00:11:52,512 --> 00:11:54,014
Oh?

206
00:11:57,017 --> 00:12:00,954
Hahaha... Are you going to kill me next?

207
00:12:01,021 --> 00:12:02,956
Yeah...

208
00:12:03,023 --> 00:12:06,526
If no one dies, someone will be killed.

209
00:12:10,530 --> 00:12:12,532
It's okay.

210
00:12:23,543 --> 00:12:26,480
(Kuroiwa) Ha, I finally found it.

211
00:12:26,546 --> 00:12:28,482
(Ohara) What happened?

212
00:12:28,548 --> 00:12:30,984
(Kuroiwa) Is it okay to interview you?

213
00:12:31,051 --> 00:12:34,988
(Ohara) I stayed in my room all last night.

214
00:12:36,490 --> 00:12:40,927
(Kuroiwa) Is there anyone who can prove that?

215
00:12:40,994 --> 00:12:44,998
>> No, I don't talk to almost anyone.

216
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,935
(Kuroiwa) Are you also with Manami?

217
00:12:49,002 --> 00:12:52,005
(Ohara) I don't have the courage to talk to you.

218
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:57,444
Actually, Manami-san →

219
00:12:57,511 --> 00:13:00,447
He's my lifesaver.

220
00:13:00,514 --> 00:13:01,948
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

221
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:07,020
(Ohara's voice) When my workplace was the worst and I wanted to disappear...

222
00:13:08,522 --> 00:13:10,457
(Manami) [Footsteps]

223
00:13:10,524 --> 00:13:13,026
>> [Wow! ] (Ohara's voice) He stopped me.

224
00:13:14,528 --> 00:13:17,964
(Ohara's voice) Life and sex? Is it something like...?

225
00:13:18,031 --> 00:13:21,034
It must have been a very exciting situation.

226
00:13:22,536 --> 00:13:27,974
It's no good, but from that time →

227
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:32,479
I wish we could be lovers.

228
00:13:32,546 --> 00:13:34,981
Not my love or anything.

229
00:13:36,483 --> 00:13:41,988
(Kuroiwa) Well... I can't help it, I fell in love with him.

230
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:46,493
Oh, no, it's not that I like you or anything.

231
00:13:47,994 --> 00:13:52,432
>> What if next I die→

232
00:13:52,499 --> 00:13:54,935
What do you think? (Kuroiwa) Huh?

233
00:13:55,001 --> 00:13:59,940
>> Manami-san, I don't think you'll notice even if I die.

234
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:02,442
(Kuroiwa) Please don't say that!

235
00:14:02,509 --> 00:14:05,946
As long as I'm alive... As long as I'm alive→

236
00:14:06,012 --> 00:14:10,016
Maybe you'll be able to turn your attention to me.

237
00:14:17,524 --> 00:14:20,460
(Kuroiwa) Good morning. It's early.

238
00:14:20,527 --> 00:14:24,464
>> In the end, no one died. (Kuroiwa) Yes.

239
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:26,533
>> Good...

240
00:14:35,976 --> 00:14:38,912
Ah, I slept well. (Kuroiwa) Good morning.

241
00:14:38,979 --> 00:14:40,981
>> Good morning.

242
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:46,987
(yawn)

243
00:14:53,994 --> 00:14:55,996
(Emoto) Huh…｡

244
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:07,440
What? this.

245
00:15:07,507 --> 00:15:09,509
(Emoto) Cup.

246
00:15:11,011 --> 00:15:13,446
Yes?

247
00:15:13,513 --> 00:15:15,949
It's such an easy thing to exchange.

248
00:15:16,016 --> 00:15:17,951
(Emoto) With this cup→

249
00:15:18,018 --> 00:15:20,453
Be determined to get out of here alive.

250
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,455
What do you mean?

251
00:15:22,522 --> 00:15:24,958
You were about to die yesterday.

252
00:15:25,025 --> 00:15:27,460
Please stir me up and make me go mad.

253
00:15:27,527 --> 00:15:29,963
Maybe eavesdropping?

254
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:32,966
(Kuroiwa) Excuse me, what are you talking about?

255
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:36,903
>> I... I don't intend to kill anyone.

256
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:40,473
Huh... Oh, what a shame.

257
00:15:45,979 --> 00:15:47,914
(Kuroiwa) I don't know what it is, but →

258
00:15:47,981 --> 00:15:49,916
I drink too. >> Huh?

259
00:15:49,983 --> 00:15:52,485
(Arizaki) Uh-huh. (Kuroiwa) Woo-hoo.

260
00:15:54,487 --> 00:15:56,423
>> Kuah!

261
00:15:56,489 --> 00:15:58,925
I'll get out of here alive.

262
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:00,493
Haha.

263
00:16:03,496 --> 00:16:05,932
That...

264
00:16:05,999 --> 00:16:08,435
This might be a bit dangerous...

265
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:09,936
(Emoto) Huh?

266
00:16:10,003 --> 00:16:12,005
Hey!

267
00:16:14,507 --> 00:16:16,443
(Kuroiwa) Erizaki-san!? (Emoto) Hey!

268
00:16:16,509 --> 00:16:20,513
(Speaker) Congratulations, you have achieved your quota.

269
00:16:22,515 --> 00:16:24,951
(Yuriko's voice) Are you okay? Manami-chan.

270
00:16:25,018 --> 00:16:27,954
(Yuriko) It's rare that I can't see a read mark for an entire day.

271
00:16:28,021 --> 00:16:30,957
(Iori) Are you sleeping with my love 24/7?

272
00:16:31,024 --> 00:16:32,959
Well, if that's the case, we'll never have sex.

273
00:16:33,026 --> 00:16:35,895
Has that kid ever broken a promise like that?

274
00:16:35,962 --> 00:16:38,398
...No.

275
00:16:38,465 --> 00:16:40,900
(Yuriko) Would you like to go to Manami-chan's apartment once... once?

276
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:42,902
(Iori) It's overprotective.

277
00:16:42,969 --> 00:16:45,905
It's not my daughter, so it's okay.

278
00:16:45,972 --> 00:16:47,907
Are you an adult detective?

279
00:16:47,974 --> 00:16:52,412
Are there no adults or children in such an abnormal situation?

280
00:16:52,479 --> 00:16:54,481
I just don't want it to be too late.

281
00:16:55,982 --> 00:16:57,917
Okay, let's go. >> Yeah!

282
00:16:57,984 --> 00:16:59,486
Let's go, hurry, hurry!

283
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:05,959
(Kuroiwa) The kabosu is probably poisonous.

284
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:09,462
>> I don't have a cup...

285
00:17:09,529 --> 00:17:11,464
(Manami) That doesn't matter.

286
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:15,034
>> But yesterday, you were having trouble with Nikki.

287
00:17:15,969 --> 00:17:19,606
(Manami) Just a moment... let's go back to the room.

288
00:17:19,672 --> 00:17:21,674
Let's talk properly.

289
00:17:22,375 --> 00:17:25,311
(chime)

290
00:17:25,378 --> 00:17:27,380
(2 people) Huh…｡

291
00:17:28,882 --> 00:17:30,817
(Kiryu) Whoa. (Iori) Wow.

292
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:32,819
(Kiryu) There's no room, Manami.

293
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:35,321
I'm an intruder, though. Is he caught red-handed?

294
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:38,825
(Kiryu) No, no, I've also received a guard key.

295
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:41,828
When I came to see it because I was worried, I couldn't even see the monitor.

296
00:17:41,895 --> 00:17:45,331
If you're not here... a pension?

297
00:17:45,398 --> 00:17:48,334
(Iori) Was the signal that bad over there?

298
00:17:48,401 --> 00:17:50,403
Were you connected until now?

299
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:57,277
(Emoto) Erizaki has always taken great care of himself.

300
00:17:57,343 --> 00:18:01,781
``You're a comrade,'' he said, acting like an older brother.

301
00:18:01,848 --> 00:18:03,850
Even though you're younger.

302
00:18:05,852 --> 00:18:08,855
I wanted him to be alive.

303
00:18:10,356 --> 00:18:13,793
(Manami) Yeah... really.

304
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:15,862
regrettable.

305
00:18:18,364 --> 00:18:21,801
>> I'm a freak at heart.

306
00:18:21,868 --> 00:18:23,803
(Manami) Huh?

307
00:18:23,870 --> 00:18:26,306
>>Probably always as a father→

308
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:29,309
I think it was because he had been beaten.

309
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:32,812
It can't even kill insects.

310
00:18:32,879 --> 00:18:36,816
I don't have the courage to kill someone...

311
00:18:36,883 --> 00:18:39,819
(Manami) That's right.

312
00:18:39,886 --> 00:18:41,821
>> I want to change myself →

313
00:18:41,888 --> 00:18:44,891
I grumbled and joined the group…｡

314
00:18:46,392 --> 00:18:48,328
It was easy.

315
00:18:48,394 --> 00:18:51,331
Don't yell or make a fuss →

316
00:18:51,397 --> 00:18:53,766
I cheated it.

317
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:58,838
But inside, I was still scared.

318
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:04,344
(Manami) I'm glad he didn't have the courage to kill me.

319
00:19:06,346 --> 00:19:10,283
>> Even though EITO was scared of dying every day →

320
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:12,785
Don't force yourself to look cool.

321
00:19:12,852 --> 00:19:14,354
(Manami) Yeah...｡

322
00:19:15,855 --> 00:19:18,858
>> Those guys are strong.

323
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:24,797
Why did those people who worked so hard to survive die?

324
00:19:24,864 --> 00:19:27,367
Am I even alive?

325
00:19:28,868 --> 00:19:30,870
(Manami) That's not what I'm talking about.

326
00:19:32,372 --> 00:19:35,808
>> But “outlaw frame” →

327
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:39,312
I'm sure you'll find it soon.

328
00:19:39,379 --> 00:19:41,381
(Manami) No...

329
00:19:42,882 --> 00:19:46,319
It's a ``straight frame'', Emo-san.

330
00:19:46,386 --> 00:19:49,822
>> Straight? Where are you...

331
00:19:49,889 --> 00:19:53,259
(Manami) When I was late, I tried to stuff my little finger in there as an apology.

332
00:19:53,326 --> 00:19:57,764
Two years ago, I gave away one extra sagyoza at a Chinese restaurant in town.

333
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:59,766
Always remember →

334
00:19:59,832 --> 00:20:02,268
They still give me a lot of gyoza.

335
00:20:02,335 --> 00:20:05,271
Say things like ``I understand.''

336
00:20:05,338 --> 00:20:09,776
Clumsily looking forward and being strong→

337
00:20:09,842 --> 00:20:12,779
Living straight.

338
00:20:12,845 --> 00:20:14,781
I like that.

339
00:20:14,847 --> 00:20:18,351
It doesn't matter if you're strong or weak!

340
00:20:21,354 --> 00:20:25,358
(Manami) I believe in you... about Emossan.

341
00:20:30,863 --> 00:20:32,865
(cough cough)

342
00:20:38,871 --> 00:20:48,314
♪～

343
00:20:48,381 --> 00:20:51,818
(Takamine) What are you doing tomorrow?

344
00:20:51,884 --> 00:20:53,753
(Kiryu) Go out to the countryside.

345
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:57,757
(Takamine) Travel? Haha, it's easy going.

346
00:20:57,824 --> 00:21:00,259
(Kiryu) I wish it were.

347
00:21:00,326 --> 00:21:02,762
Check on someone important to you.

348
00:21:03,329 --> 00:21:04,897
(Takamine) Manami Tanizaki…｡

349
00:21:04,964 --> 00:21:06,966
Come on.

350
00:21:08,001 --> 00:21:10,436
They're persistent, as expected from the police.

351
00:21:10,503 --> 00:21:17,677
♪～

352
00:21:17,744 --> 00:21:19,412
what happened? Suddenly.

353
00:21:19,479 --> 00:21:23,416
That's a bad idea, even though you're a detective.

354
00:21:23,483 --> 00:21:24,951
(noise)

355
00:21:25,018 --> 00:21:28,788
(Manami) Ah... didn't you hear any noise just now?

356
00:21:28,855 --> 00:21:30,923
(Kuroiwa) Are deer mating again?

357
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:34,427
(Manami) No, it felt like something was knocking on the wall.

358
00:21:34,494 --> 00:21:36,496
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

359
00:21:37,997 --> 00:21:40,433
Ah... Emo-san?

360
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,435
(Manami) Oh, that's true.

361
00:21:42,502 --> 00:21:44,437
(sound of tapping)

362
00:21:44,504 --> 00:21:51,010
♪～

363
00:21:53,946 --> 00:21:55,882
(Kuroiwa) Nothing in particular.

364
00:21:55,948 --> 00:21:57,884
Why are you here...?

365
00:21:57,950 --> 00:21:59,886
(Manami) Hmm, it hurts when it's warm.

366
00:21:59,952 --> 00:22:01,888
(Kuroiwa) Are you okay? (Manami) Yeah...｡

367
00:22:01,954 --> 00:22:04,490
(Kuroiwa) You're not sleeping, are you? Manami-san.

368
00:22:04,557 --> 00:22:08,227
(Manami) I'm not sleeping! I haven't slept with anyone for a week now.

369
00:22:08,294 --> 00:22:11,230
(Kuroiwa) No, not that one.

370
00:22:11,297 --> 00:22:12,732
(Manami) Huh... what?

371
00:22:12,799 --> 00:22:17,236
(Kuroiwa) No. Are you forcing yourself to make it brighter?

372
00:22:17,303 --> 00:22:19,238
(Manami) Huh?

373
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:21,808
(Kuroiwa) Why don't you take a break?

374
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:28,748
(Manami) No, if I rest now→

375
00:22:28,815 --> 00:22:30,817
absolutely….

376
00:22:32,318 --> 00:22:35,321
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san!? Huh...｡

377
00:22:37,323 --> 00:22:39,258
(noise)

378
00:22:39,325 --> 00:22:41,327
(Manami) Huh?

379
00:22:45,331 --> 00:22:48,835
(Manami) Ah...ha...｡

380
00:22:53,272 --> 00:22:54,841
(Manami) Huh!?

381
00:22:54,907 --> 00:22:58,344
Emo-san! Emo-san!

382
00:22:59,345 --> 00:23:01,848
Emo-san!!
